    q: "Is it safe to keep using my dishwasher if it's leaking?",
    a: "Depends on volume and source. A small puddle once per cycle from a worn door gasket is not an emergency, you can use the unit while we schedule the repair. Continuous dripping during the fill cycle (water inlet valve stuck open) or active streaming during the wash phase requires shutting it off; the volume can damage flooring and cabinetry within hours. We treat continuous-leak calls as same-day priority.",
